                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d460">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">793.94/4375: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Minister in China (<persName corresp="#p_JNT1" type="from"
                            >Johnson</persName>) to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Peiping</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1932-02-24T12:00:00+08:00"
                            >February 24, 1932—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received February 24—4:10
                        a.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>266. Harbin reports that from railway and Japanese sources it has been learned
                    that old Kirin troops have occupied several stations on eastern section of
                    Chinese Eastern Railway. Japanese claim that these forces have looted Japanese
                    properties and that Japanese and Koreans endangered have appealed for military
                    protection which is being considered. <persName corresp="#p_MC1">Ma
                        Chan-shan</persName> left Harbin February 22 to establish provincial
                    government at Tsitsihar.</p>
                <closer>For the Minister:<lb/>
                    <signed>
                        <persName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Perkins</hi>
                        </persName>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
